      "topic": "number_algebra",
      "skill_tag": "binomial_theorem",
      "parts": [
        {
          "label": "a",
          "body": "Write down an expression for the general term in the expansion.",
          "marks": 2,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "apply the binomial theorem to the two bracket terms"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$\\binom{6}{k}(x^2)^{6-k}\\left(-\\dfrac{2}{x}\\right)^{k} = \\binom{6}{k}(-2)^k x^{12-3k}$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$\\binom{6}{k}(-2)^k x^{12-3k}$",
          "solution": "$$T_k = \\binom{6}{k}(x^2)^{6-k}\\left(-\\frac{2}{x}\\right)^{k} = \\binom{6}{k}(-2)^k x^{12-3k}$$",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(binomial(6, 1)*(-2)**1, -12)",
            "Eq(12 - 3*1, 9)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "body": "Hence find the term independent of $x$.",
          "marks": 3,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "set the index to zero: $12 - 3k = 0$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$k = 4$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$\\binom{6}{4}(-2)^4 = 15 \\times 16 = 240$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$240$",
          "solution": "The term independent of $x$ needs $12 - 3k = 0$, so $k = 4$:$$\\binom{6}{4}(-2)^4 = 15 \\cdot 16 = 240.$$",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(solve(Eq(12 - 3*x, 0), x)[0], 4)",
            "Eq(binomial(6, 4)*(-2)**4, 240)",
            "Eq(expand((x**2 - 2/x)**6).coeff(x, 0), 240)"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "contextIntro": "Consider the expansion of $\\left(x^2 - \\dfrac{2}{x}\\right)^{6}$."
    },
    {
