              "note": "only $x = 2$ is real"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "only real root: $x = 2$",
          "solution": "The quadratic factor has discriminant $$\\Delta = 1^2 - 4(2)(3) = -23 < 0,$$ so it has no real zeros, and the only real root of $p(x) = 0$ is $x = 2$.",
          "verify": [
