              "note": "$z^6 = 2^6\\big(\\cos 2\\pi + i\\sin 2\\pi\\big)$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$\\cos 2\\pi = 1$, $\\sin 2\\pi = 0$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$z^6 = 64$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$z^6 = 64$",
          "solution": "$z = 2\\operatorname{cis}\\dfrac{\\pi}{3}$, so by de Moivre$$z^6 = 2^6\\operatorname{cis}(2\\pi) = 64(1 + 0i) = 64.$$",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(simplify((1 + sqrt(3)*I)**6), 64)",
            "Eq(2**6, 64)",
            "Eq(6*pi/3, 2*pi)"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "contextIntro": "Let $z = 1 + \\sqrt{3}\\,i$."
    },
    {
