      "parts": [
        {
          "label": "a",
          "body": "Using the identity for $\\tan(A + B)$, show that $\\tan 75^{\\circ} = 2 + \\sqrt{3}$.",
          "marks": 4,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "write $75^{\\circ} = 45^{\\circ} + 30^{\\circ}$ and apply $\\tan(A+B) = \\dfrac{\\tan A + \\tan B}{1 - \\tan A\\tan B}$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$\\dfrac{1 + \\tfrac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}}{1 - \\tfrac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}} = \\dfrac{\\sqrt{3} + 1}{\\sqrt{3} - 1}$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "rationalise the denominator"
            },
            {
              "mark": "AG",
              "note": "$\\dfrac{(\\sqrt{3}+1)^2}{2} = \\dfrac{4 + 2\\sqrt{3}}{2} = 2 + \\sqrt{3}$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$\\tan 75^{\\circ} = 2 + \\sqrt{3}$",
          "solution": "$$\\tan 75^{\\circ} = \\frac{\\tan 45^{\\circ} + \\tan 30^{\\circ}}{1 - \\tan 45^{\\circ}\\tan 30^{\\circ}} = \\frac{1 + \\tfrac{1}{\\sqrt3}}{1 - \\tfrac{1}{\\sqrt3}} = \\frac{\\sqrt3 + 1}{\\sqrt3 - 1}$$Multiplying top and bottom by $(\\sqrt3 + 1)$:$$\\frac{(\\sqrt3 + 1)^2}{3 - 1} = \\frac{4 + 2\\sqrt3}{2} = 2 + \\sqrt{3}.$$",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(simplify((1 + 1/sqrt(3))/(1 - 1/sqrt(3)) - (2 + sqrt(3))), 0)",
            "Eq(simplify(tan(5*pi/12) - (2 + sqrt(3))), 0)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "body": "Hence find the exact value of $\\tan 15^{\\circ}$.",
          "marks": 2,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "$\\tan 15^{\\circ} = \\dfrac{1}{\\tan 75^{\\circ}}$ (complementary angles)"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$\\dfrac{1}{2 + \\sqrt{3}} = 2 - \\sqrt{3}$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$\\tan 15^{\\circ} = 2 - \\sqrt{3}$",
          "solution": "Since $15^{\\circ}$ and $75^{\\circ}$ are complementary, $\\tan 15^{\\circ} = \\cot 75^{\\circ}$:$$\\tan 15^{\\circ} = \\frac{1}{2 + \\sqrt3} = \\frac{2 - \\sqrt3}{(2+\\sqrt3)(2-\\sqrt3)} = 2 - \\sqrt{3}.$$",
          "verify": [
